						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in a field to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1555 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1477, Rākshasa, Chaitra ba. 12,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1555 A.D., April 18 (Thursday).</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to register certain gift (details lost) to god Virūpāksha of the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> village Narasāpuram <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kṛishṇarāyapuram in Pullēṭi-māgāṇi in Jagtāpi-Gutti-sīma by the son (name lost) of Yeramarāju of Bhāradvāja-<hi rend="italic">gōtra,</hi> Āapastaṁba-<hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi> and Ṛik-<hi rend="italic">s11ākha.</hi> Mentions <hi rend="italic">mantramūrti</hi> Basvaya and Gōvindaya as signatories.</p>						

						</summary>
